      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "[Your Company Letterhead]\n\nDate: [Current Date]\n\nTo: [Recipient Name] and Relevant Department Heads\n\nSubject: Comprehensive KYC Compliance Memo for New Onboarding Process\n\nDear Colleagues,\n\nThis memo serves to outline our newly established adherence to rigorous Know Your Customer (KYC) and Anti-Money Laundering (AML) compliance standards in our onboarding process. As part of our unwavering commitment to regulatory adherence, our compliance engine employs an automated scanning tool that meticulously verifies the inclusion of all pertinent legal terminology and compliance steps.\n\nSecured KYC protocols will now comprise the following stages and terms:\n\n1. Client Information Collection: Obtain accurate and complete basic information including full name, address, date and place of birth, citizenship, ID number, and contact information, thereby fulfilling the initial customer identification requirements.\n\n2. Customer Due Diligence (CDD): Conduct both 'sustained' and heightened due diligence based on customer classification per regulatory standards. This will include background checks, verification against EDD and watchlists, and ongoing monitoring.\n\n3. Risk Assessment: Implement a rigorous risk-based approach to evaluate ongoing and potential risks associated with each customer. Procedures should align with the International Standards on Risk Management.\n\n4. Beneficial Ownership Determination",
      "source": "target",
